Kinyuru Munuhe @kinyurumunuhe Health Cabinet Secretary Sicily Kariuki has invited applications for the position of non-executive chairperson at Kenya Medical Supplies Authority (Kemsa). “Written applications should include a curriculum vitae (CV) and clearly indicate application for the post of chairperson. Closing date for the application will be on February 25 at 11am,” she said. The candidates must have at least a degree certificate in a relevant discipline, at least 15 years experience in matters related to healthcare or business management and satisfy the requirements of Chapter Six of the Constitution. They must also have clearance certificates from KRA, DCI, CRB, Helb and EACC. The new board chair is expected to ensure all Kemsa stores have real-time CCTV surveillance, among other policy guidelines.